        {
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "{\"message\":\"Fixed CVSS v4.0 vectors by adding mandatory SC, SI, SA metrics and replacing invalid VC/VI/VA values (no 'M' in v4.0). Adjusted or nullified OWASP/MITRE mappings that were flagged as potentially unrelated while retaining original IDs and element/dataflow names.\",\"threats\":[{\"id\":1,\"element\":\"User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Attacker spoofs a legitimate user identity/session to submit prompts and drive unintended agent actions.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Strong authentication if applicable; signed/HttpOnly/SameSite cookies; CSRF protection; device fingerprinting and anomaly detection; rate limiting and CAPTCHA for public endpoints; short session lifetime and rotation.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":2,\"element\":\"User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Users deny having issued prompts that caused actions or data access (lack of non-repudiation).\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"End-to-end request logging with timestamps, user/session IDs, IPs; signed request IDs; immutable append-only logs; retain final answers, tool calls metadata and hashes to prove integrity.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":3,\"element\":\"LLM Provider (OpenAI/HF/Ollama)\",\"threat_description\":\"Agent connects to a spoofed or malicious LLM endpoint (DNS poisoning/MitM) leading to manipulated responses or API key theft.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0010: ML Supply Chain Compromise\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce TLS 1.2+ with cert validation and optional certificate pinning; verify host allowlist; use official SDKs; validate response signatures if supported; restrict egress via firewall/DNS policies.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":4,\"element\":\"LLM Provider (OpenAI/HF/Ollama)\",\"threat_description\":\"Provider repudiates responses or usage; lack of traceability of prompts/responses for billing/security investigations.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Store request/response transcripts and request IDs; enable provider-side logs; use signed receipts/webhooks where available; include deterministic request headers and nonces.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":5,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Session hijack/CSRF leads the UI to accept actions as another user.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable CSRF protection; strict session handling (HttpOnly, SameSite, secure); origin/referrer checks; OAuth/OpenID Connect for auth; rotate tokens; TLS everywhere.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":6,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI\",\"threat_description\":\"UI code or state is tampered via XSS/DOM injection or malicious Streamlit components, altering inputs sent to the agent.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\",\"mitigation\":\"Escape/sanitize all untrusted content; avoid unsafe HTML; CSP with strict directives; limit third-party components; input validation; dependency pinning and SCA.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:L/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":7,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient audit trails allow repudiation of UI submissions or displayed outputs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Structured, immutable logging of user actions, prompts, and result rendering events; correlate UI event IDs with agent/tool logs; time sync and log shipping.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":8,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive info (API keys, system prompts, stack traces) displayed to end users through error banners or debug panels.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Disable debug in prod; centralized error handling with redaction; never render secrets; redact PII; content security policy; segregate admin diagnostics from user UI.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":9,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Flooding UI endpoints leads to resource exhaustion or excessive LLM invocations.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Rate limiting, request quotas per IP/user; global concurrency caps; queue/backpressure; circuit breakers; caching; WAF/CDN.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":10,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI\",\"threat_description\":\"UI enables privilege escalation via unsafe execution hooks or excessive capabilities (e.g., executing arbitrary Python through components).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency\",\"mitigation\":\"Disable/avoid eval-like features; sandbox untrusted components; run with least OS privileges; code reviews for UI callbacks; dependency hardening.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:P/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":11,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Spoofed tools or forged tool outputs mislead the agent (tool identity not authenticated).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency\",\"mitigation\":\"Whitelist tools by explicit, signed registration; verify tool caller identity; attach HMAC/signatures to tool results; bind tool schema to strict parsers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":12,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Prompt injection manipulates the agent to exfiltrate secrets, call dangerous tools, or alter chain logic.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection\",\"mitigation\":\"Segment user input from system/tool instructions; apply allowlists for tools; context filtering and output validators; instruction hierarchy enforcement; content/policy classifiers; limit tool arguments; use constrained decoding and schema validation.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":13,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of action traceability lets the agent repudiate tool calls or data access decisions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Comprehensive agent telemetry: log prompts, tool calls, parameters, observations, token counts; hash and timestamp each step; secure log storage; correlation IDs spanning UI\u2192agent\u2192tools.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":14,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"System prompt and secrets leakage via agent outputs or error traces.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Never inject secrets into model context; secret redaction; response post-processing to block prompt/secret patterns; use tools for data retrieval instead of embedding secrets; disable verbose traces in prod; test with red-team prompts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":15,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Unbounded tool/LLM calling creates runaway costs and service degradation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Max-steps and token caps; timeouts; cost and call quotas per session/user; loop detection; circuit breakers; exponential backoff and global rate limits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":16,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Agent escalates privileges by invoking powerful local tools or code execution paths beyond intended scope.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency\",\"mitigation\":\"Run agent under least-privileged OS user; disable shell/code tools in production; sandbox (seccomp, containers); permission model for tool use; human-in-the-loop for sensitive actions.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":17,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher (tools.py & utils.py)\",\"threat_description\":\"Unauthorized caller spoofs the agent to invoke tools directly.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Internal auth for IPC calls (local tokens); process identity checks; restrict import paths; run dispatcher on loopback only; mTLS for inter-process HTTP if used.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":18,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher (tools.py & utils.py)\",\"threat_description\":\"Tool parameters are tampered (e.g., SQL injection or path traversal) leading to unintended queries or file access.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\",\"mitigation\":\"Strict input schemas and validation; parameterized SQL; denylist of dangerous SQL; allowlist tables/columns; sanitize paths; escape user-controlled values; use ORM with query builders.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":19,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher (tools.py & utils.py)\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of auditable logs allows repudiation of executed tools/queries.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Structured logging of tool name, parameters, SQL text with parameter values, row counts, timing, caller identity; tamper-evident log storage.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":20,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher (tools.py & utils.py)\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive DB data or file contents may be over-exposed to the agent beyond least privilege.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0037: Data from Local System\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Row/column-level filtering; data classification; output redaction; limit query breadth; PII masking; minimize tool return payloads; access controls per tool.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":21,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher (tools.py & utils.py)\",\"threat_description\":\"Expensive or unbounded queries/tools cause resource exhaustion.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Query timeouts and LIMITs; rate limits; concurrency controls; circuit breakers; pre-compute indexes; cache common results; cancel queries on session end.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":22,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher (tools.py & utils.py)\",\"threat_description\":\"Dispatcher invokes OS commands, network, or file operations enabling privilege escalation/escape.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency\",\"mitigation\":\"Remove shelling-out; restrict OS capabilities (seccomp/apparmor); containerize tools; least-privilege filesystem access; egress firewall; code review for tool safety.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":23,\"element\":\"SQLite DB (transactions.db)\",\"threat_description\":\"DB file or contents are tampered (unauthorized writes/schema changes).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"File permissions (read-only where possible); run as non-root; mount DB read-only for read-mostly; SQLite integrity_check; backups with checksums; application-level integrity constraints.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":24,\"element\":\"SQLite DB (transactions.db)\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of audit trail for data changes enables repudiation of modifications.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Append-only audit table with triggers recording old/new values and actor; sign audit rows; time sync; protect logs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":25,\"element\":\"SQLite DB (transactions.db)\",\"threat_description\":\"Unauthorized access to DB file discloses sensitive transactional data.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0037: Data from Local System\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Restrictive filesystem ACLs; encrypt DB at rest (SQLite SEE/SQLCipher); avoid storing secrets; secure backups; do not mount DB into UI container layers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":26,\"element\":\"SQLite DB (transactions.db)\",\"threat_description\":\"DB locked or corrupted causing read failures and outages.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Busy timeouts; read-only mode for readers; limit long transactions; periodic VACUUM/ANALYZE; health checks and automatic recovery from backups.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":27,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml)\",\"threat_description\":\"Configuration/secrets tampering changes API keys or tool/DB endpoints.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Immutable config in production; read-only mounts; signature/ checksum verification on startup; least-privileged file permissions; 4-eyes change control.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":28,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml)\",\"threat_description\":\"No change history leads to repudiation of config modifications.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Version control (private repo); signed commits; change tickets; checksum snapshots; store effective runtime config to an audit log on startup.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":29,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml)\",\"threat_description\":\"Secrets/API keys disclosed via repo leaks, logs, or process dumps.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0055: Unsecured Credentials\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Use a secrets manager; avoid committing .env; restrict read access; redact logs; rotate keys; avoid loading secrets into prompts; use env vars injected at runtime.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":30,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml)\",\"threat_description\":\"Deleting or corrupting config prevents app/agent from starting or operating.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Read-only mounts; startup validation with clear errors; fallback defaults for non-sensitive values; high-availability secret storage; backups and restore playbooks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":31,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Streamlit UI (User input)\",\"threat_description\":\"Prompt tampering/injection to manipulate downstream agent and tools.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection\",\"mitigation\":\"Input validation and size caps; treat user input as untrusted context; strip/annotate instructions; use content filters; isolate user text from system prompts; disable markdown HTML where unsafe.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:A/VC:L/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":32,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Streamlit UI (User input)\",\"threat_description\":\"User inadvertently submits sensitive data that could leak via logs or LLM context.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Client-side warnings; server-side redaction (SSN, keys); prevent storing raw prompts; PII detection; selective context inclusion; per-tenant data boundaries.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:A/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":33,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Streamlit UI (User input)\",\"threat_description\":\"Flood of large prompts or file uploads causing resource exhaustion and LLM cost spikes.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Request size limits; rate limiting; per-user quotas; early reject overly long inputs; streaming with backpressure; pre-check token estimates before forwarding to LLM.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":34,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI -> User (Browser) (Output)\",\"threat_description\":\"Response tampering (e.g., MitM, malicious extensions) injects scripts or alters results.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\",\"mitigation\":\"TLS; CSP; Subresource Integrity for assets; disable inline scripts; no unsafe HTML rendering; escape model outputs; optional signed responses in zero-trust contexts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":35,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI -> User (Browser) (Output)\",\"threat_description\":\"Outputs reveal system prompts, stack traces, or sensitive data.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0056: LLM Meta Prompt Extraction\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Output filters/redactors; safe error pages; block tokens matching secret patterns; evaluate prompts for leakage before rendering; role-based masking.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":36,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI -> User (Browser) (Output)\",\"threat_description\":\"Very large responses or streaming floods overwhelm the browser/client.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Chunked streaming with limits; truncate long outputs; pagination; client timeouts; server-side response size caps.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":37,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI -> LangChain ReAct Agent (submit)\",\"threat_description\":\"Submission payload is tampered (e.g., injected control tokens) altering agent behavior.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection\",\"mitigation\":\"Strict message schema; escape user content; separate channels for instructions vs data; sanitize/normalize inputs; use guardrails/policy models before agent consumption.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":38,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI -> LangChain ReAct Agent (submit)\",\"threat_description\":\"Submission includes or exposes sensitive info that propagates into logs/LLM context.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Minimize logging of inputs; redact secrets; PII detection; tenant isolation; encrypt in transit (loopback TLS if crossing hosts).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":39,\"element\":\"Streamlit UI -> LangChain ReAct Agent (submit)\",\"threat_description\":\"Burst of submissions overwhelms agent pipelines and queues.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Backpressure between UI and agent; per-session concurrency caps; request shedding; priority queues; circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":40,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> Streamlit UI (final answer)\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered final answer (e.g., injected HTML/JS) before rendering.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\",\"mitigation\":\"Sanitize/escape model outputs; disallow raw HTML rendering; content filters; neutralize links; safe Markdown rendering settings.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":41,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> Streamlit UI (final answer)\",\"threat_description\":\"Final answer includes sensitive data or prompts that should not be exposed.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Apply post-answer redaction and policy checks; allowlist visible fields; mask PII; enforce tenant context constraints before display.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":42,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> Streamlit UI (final answer)\",\"threat_description\":\"Very large answers or infinite streams overwhelm UI pipeline.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Response size/time caps; streaming with token budgets; cancelation support; truncation with user consent for expansion.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":43,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> Tool Dispatcher (tool call)\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered tool call parameters (from compromised agent state) cause unintended operations.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency\",\"mitigation\":\"Strict tool schemas; parameter validation; allowlist of operations/resources; max rows and timeouts; require confirmation for sensitive tools (HITL).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":44,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> Tool Dispatcher (tool call)\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive data embedded in tool call arguments leaks to logs or other components.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0037: Data from Local System\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Avoid logging secrets; redact parameters; minimize argument payload; use in-memory passing; encrypt logs at rest with access controls.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":45,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> Tool Dispatcher (tool call)\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive tool call volume causes queue saturation and resource depletion.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Rate limit per session; concurrency pools; backpressure to agent; circuit breakers and retries with jitter; step budget enforcement.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":46,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher -> LangChain ReAct Agent (Observation)\",\"threat_description\":\"Tool results tampered or forged, misleading the agent.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\",\"mitigation\":\"Sign tool outputs; integrity checks (hash of query + parameters + rows); transmit over authenticated channel; verify schema/shape upon receipt.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":47,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher -> LangChain ReAct Agent (Observation)\",\"threat_description\":\"Observations reveal more data than necessary (over-broad rows).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Apply LIMIT and column selection; mask PII; partition/tenant filters; redact before returning; enforce max payload bytes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":48,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher -> LangChain ReAct Agent (Observation)\",\"threat_description\":\"Large result sets overwhelm the agent's memory or token budgets.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Row caps and pagination; sample/aggregate; early truncation; stream incrementally with stop conditions; enforce token budget checks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":49,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher -> SQLite DB (transactions.db) (SQL query)\",\"threat_description\":\"Query text tampered (dynamic string concatenation) enabling unintended writes or data exposure.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Parameterized queries only; prepared statements; avoid string building; static query templates; least privilege (read-only) connections.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":50,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher -> SQLite DB (transactions.db) (SQL query)\",\"threat_description\":\"Query parameters include sensitive data that may be logged by SQLite or OS.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0037: Data from Local System\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Disable SQL logging in prod; scrub parameters before logs; secure DB temporary files; use in-memory parameters; encrypt swap/disable core dumps.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":51,\"element\":\"Tool Dispatcher -> SQLite DB (transactions.db) (SQL query)\",\"threat_description\":\"Expensive queries (full scans, no indexes) starve DB, causing timeouts.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Indexes; LIMIT + WHERE; query planner hints; timeout settings; rate limits; reject long-running queries; analyze and optimize queries.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":52,\"element\":\"SQLite DB (transactions.db) -> Tool Dispatcher (rows)\",\"threat_description\":\"Rows tampered (corrupt DB/file) causing incorrect observations.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"DB integrity_check; checksums; verify row counts/types; fail closed on corruption; restore from trusted backups.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":53,\"element\":\"SQLite DB (transactions.db) -> Tool Dispatcher (rows)\",\"threat_description\":\"Returned rows include sensitive fields not intended for the agent.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0037: Data from Local System\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Projection of explicit columns; view-based access; data masking; confidential attributes filtered in SQL layer.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":54,\"element\":\"SQLite DB (transactions.db) -> Tool Dispatcher (rows)\",\"threat_description\":\"Huge result sets cause memory/processing exhaustion.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"LIMIT; pagination/streaming; cap payload bytes; cancel queries exceeding thresholds; backpressure to caller.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":55,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml) -> LangChain ReAct Agent (Agent config & API key)\",\"threat_description\":\"Config values tampered in transit/load (e.g., overridden by env) altering agent behavior.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0010: ML Supply Chain Compromise\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM03: 2025 Supply Chain\",\"mitigation\":\"Load-order hardening; only read from trusted paths; verify checksums/signatures; lock down environment variable injection; assert schema and ranges for config values.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":56,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml) -> LangChain ReAct Agent (Agent config & API key)\",\"threat_description\":\"API key exposure during load (logs, exceptions, memory dumps).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0055: Unsecured Credentials\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid logging secrets; mask on print; secure memory handling; disable core dumps; role-based access to env/config; rotate keys on incident.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":57,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml) -> LangChain ReAct Agent (Agent config & API key)\",\"threat_description\":\"Missing/invalid config or key leads to agent failures and outages.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Startup validation with clear errors; fallback to degraded mode; health checks; secret manager with HA; retries with jitter.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":58,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml) -> Tool Dispatcher (Tool/DB config)\",\"threat_description\":\"DB path/params tampered to point to malicious or non-existent DB.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Validate config against allowlists; canonicalize and verify DB location; require file ownership/permissions; refuse network paths if not needed.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":59,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml) -> Tool Dispatcher (Tool/DB config)\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive config (paths, credentials) gets exposed via logs or errors.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0037: Data from Local System\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Do not log full config; mask sensitive fields; minimal error messages; separate secrets from non-secrets; limit read access.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":60,\"element\":\"Config files (.env, yaml, toml) -> Tool Dispatcher (Tool/DB config)\",\"threat_description\":\"Invalid/slow DB configs cause dispatcher unavailability.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Validate DB connectivity at startup; timeouts and retries; fall back to read-only or cached mode; circuit breaker for DB-dependent tools.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":61,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> LLM Provider (OpenAI/HF/Ollama) (API key / LLM request)\",\"threat_description\":\"Request tampering or MitM discloses API key or alters prompt.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS with cert validation/pinning; HTTPS-only; minimize key scope; rotate keys; avoid sending secrets in prompts; sign requests if supported.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:L/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":62,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> LLM Provider (OpenAI/HF/Ollama) (API key / LLM request)\",\"threat_description\":\"Prompts unintentionally exfiltrate confidential data to provider or outside tenant boundary.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Do not include secrets in prompts; provider data control settings; selective redaction; enterprise tenancy with data retention off; PHI/PII filters.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":63,\"element\":\"LangChain ReAct Agent -> LLM Provider (OpenAI/HF/Ollama) (API key / LLM request)\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive/automated requests drive cost spikes and rate-limit/DoS.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Per-user/session budgets; global quotas; adaptive rate limiting; batching; caching; preflight token estimation; hard cost ceilings.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":64,\"element\":\"LLM Provider (OpenAI/HF/Ollama) -> LangChain ReAct Agent (LLM response)\",\"threat_description\":\"Response tampering or compromised provider returns manipulated or adversarial outputs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0043: Craft Adversarial Data\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Validate outputs against schemas; toxicity/safety filters; cross-check critical answers; deterministic temperature for sensitive tasks; provider trust and SLAs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":65,\"element\":\"LLM Provider (OpenAI/HF/Ollama) -> LangChain ReAct Agent (LLM response)\",\"threat_description\":\"Responses leak other tenants\u2019 data or echo back confidential prompts.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Enterprise isolation features; no-training/retention flags; contractual DP/segregation assurances; post-response redaction; anomaly detection for out-of-scope entities.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":66,\"element\":\"LLM Provider (OpenAI/HF/Ollama) -> LangChain ReAct Agent (LLM response)\",\"threat_description\":\"Very long or looping responses consume resources and block pipelines.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Set max tokens and timeouts; stop sequences; streaming with early cutoff; cancelation support; limit retries on 429/5xx.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"}],\"is_final\":true}"
        }
    ]
}